hoha
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:fed up, bored; being a nuisance
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1963 Vincent O'Sullivan p.c. Used frequently by Northland Maori children in sense `fed up'
